## Critical Files

- **`common/chat.cpp`** — all changes go here; no other files are modified
  - New handler: insert before line 1519 (the `namespace workaround {` block), after the last existing handler `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3` ends at line 1517
  - Dispatcher: add new detection block inside `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` before the final `return std::nullopt;` at line 1690
- **`common/chat.h`** — read-only; `COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` (enum value 0) is already defined and sufficient

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1 — Add the new handler function

Insert the following static function in `common/chat.cpp` **after line 1517** (closing `}` of `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3`) and **before line 1519** (`namespace workaround {`):

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template & /* tmpl */,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {

    common_chat_params data;

    std::string system_prompt;
    std::string prompt;
    bool first_user = true;

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        auto content = msg.value("content", "");

        if (role == "system") {
            system_prompt = content;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            std::string turn_content;
            if (first_user && !system_prompt.empty()) {
                turn_content = system_prompt + "\n" + content;
                first_user = false;
            } else {
